Germany Sees No Need for Further Expansion of EFSF

-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 
2011-09-26T10:20:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/germany-sees-no-need-for-further-expansion-of-efsf.html
The German government sees no need
to expand the European Financial Stability Facility beyond the
current plans to boost the rescue fund, Finance Ministry
spokesman Martin Kotthaus told reporters at a regular press
conference in Berlin.  Less than a quarter of the EFSF’s funds have been tapped so
far, Kotthaus said. He added that  Germany ’s opposition to
further EFSF expansion includes rejecting leveraging the fund.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Brian Parkin at 
 bparkin@bloomberg.net  